                                                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="13479477" author="stack" created="Thu, 18 Oct 2012 23:29:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking critical and 0.96.0.  0.96 will be the release where we first go out modularized.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13479558" author="jesse_yates" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2012 01:28:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 lets do it! Definitely not a trivial ask though - good on ya&apos; elliot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13499270" author="eclark" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 00:26:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;VERY Raw.  I&apos;m running tests now but this patch is so huge I wanted others to take a look at it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Had to gzip this it&apos;s 13mb; I&apos;ll push this to my github)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Created an hbase-rpc module for the protobuf rpc classes (should allow someone to make an external client without relying on all of hbase)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Created an hbase-client&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Moved all exceptions into hbase-common (there were lots of other exceptions there already).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Made hbase-server depend upon hbase-client&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Moved all of the classes needed for a client into hbase-client.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up RpcEngine into RpcClientEngine and RpcServerEngine.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up ProtobufRpcEngine&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up HBaseRpc into HBaseClientRpc and HBaseServerRpc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split some enums out of their parent classes so that using BloomType and the like doesn&apos;t pull all of the io package.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fixed up tests to use the new enums.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changed HBaseClient to rely on the Protobuf response rather than using the HRegionServe&apos;s response type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13499274" author="eclark" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 00:34:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;good view of the changes: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/elliottneilclark/hbase/commit/8816b7d7236b607e450dc1281a486ec4c3b08397&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/elliottneilclark/hbase/commit/8816b7d7236b607e450dc1281a486ec4c3b08397&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13499290" author="enis" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 01:01:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just skimmed the patch w/o reviewing it. +1 for hbase-client and hbase-rpc modules. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13499295" author="jesse_yates" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 01:09:25 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up RpcEngine into RpcClientEngine and RpcServerEngine.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up ProtobufRpcEngine&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split up HBaseRpc into HBaseClientRpc and HBaseServerRpc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changed HBaseClient to rely on the Protobuf response rather than using the HRegionServe&apos;s response type.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Split some enums out of their parent classes so that using BloomType and the like doesn&apos;t pull all of the io package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any chance this can be done in another set of subtasks? Would it even make sense? Trying to keep this as small as possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13499299" author="eclark" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 01:15:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Without those things I couldn&apos;t get the client module to compile so probably not possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13499303" author="jesse_yates" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 01:18:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmmm, guess I should go read the code a little deeper before throwing out wild suggestions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But +1 on the high level.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13499305" author="enis" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2012 01:20:07 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Without those things I couldn&apos;t get the client module to compile so probably not possible.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think what Jesse means is to do these changes before the module split, and moving the files. Then we can do a more straightforward module split. wdyt? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500459" author="eclark" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 18:23:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure I&apos;ll give it a shot.  Some of the changes are when splitting the classes only become really evident after the move.  Other than that it should be pretty easy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500711" author="enis" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 23:00:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for chopping up the work and doing it piecemeal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13775270" author="stack" created="Mon, 23 Sep 2013 18:31:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
